-------------------------Message 1 ---------------------------------- 
Date: Sun, 26 Mar 2006 17:53:44
From: Klaus Geyer < klaus_geyer@gmx.net >
Subject: Aspects of Language Functioning in Different Linguistic, Didactic and Sociocultural Contexts 
 


Full Title: Aspects of Language Functioning in Different Linguistic, Didactic and Sociocultural Contexts 

Date: 26-Oct-2006 - 27-Oct-2026
Location: Vilnius, Lithuania 
Contact Person: Jovita Bagdonavi?i?t?
Meeting Email: lijola@centras.lt
Web Site: http://www.vpu.lt/get_file.php?file=dnB1X2ludGVybmV0L20vbV9maWxlcy93ZmlsZXMvZmlsZTM1MTAuZG9jO0ludGVyY29uZi5kb2M7Ow== 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)
                     French (fra)
                     German, Standard (deu)

Call Deadline: 01-Oct-2006 

Meeting Description:

2nd International Conference on Aspects of Language Functioning in Different Linguistic, Didactic and Sociocultural Contexts at Vilnius Pedagogical University, Lithuania 

We kindly invite researchers, university/school teachers and doctoral students to participate in an international conference held at Vilnius Pedagogical University and hosted by the Faculty of Foreign Languages.

Conference Topics include, but are not limited to:

-Linguistics, Sociolinguistics, Psycholinguistics, Discourse Analysis, and Pragmatics.

-Second Language Acquisition, English for Special Purposes.
-Innovative Teaching and Learning Technologies in Foreign Language Teaching.

-Sociocultural Aspects in Foreign Language Teaching.  

Conference Languages: English, French, German

Venue:
Faculty of Foreign Languages
Vilnius Pedagogical University
Studentu st. 39, LT-08106 Vilnius, Lithuania

Important deadlines:

Submission of registration forms and abstracts of presentations are due by October 1, 2006.

Participants' notification of acceptance to the conference sent via e-mail by October 5, 2006.

The conference program will be announced by October 10, 2006. 
Conference presentations are due by October 20, 2006.

Conference Fee:
Conference participant fee is 50 Lt.
The conference fee is paid at registration on the first day of the conference.

Submission of Papers:
Registration forms, abstracts of presentations and extended versions of presentations can be submitted
   
By e-mail: lijola@centras.lt
By mail: Department of the English Language Didactics (Room 210), Vilnius Pedagogical University, Studentu st. 39, LT-08106 Vilnius, Lithuania 

For more information contact:
Ms. Jovita Bagdonavi?i?t?
by e-mail: lijola@centras.lt 

Selection of conference presentations will be made according to the abstracts.

Requirements for Abstracts:
Abstracts should be written in the language of the presentation. The length of the abstract should be 800-1000 characters. 

Presentations meeting the requirements of scientific publications will be published in conference proceedings.




