1)
Date: 27-Mar-2006
From: Laura Dilley < dilley.28@osu.edu >
Subject: Buckeye Corpus of Speech Available 

	
-------------------------Message 1 ---------------------------------- 
Date: Mon, 27 Mar 2006 12:36:20
From: Laura Dilley < dilley.28@osu.edu >
Subject: Buckeye Corpus of Speech Available 
 


Dear Colleagues: 

We would like to announce the initial public release of the Buckeye Corpus
of conversational speech. The corpus contains high-quality recordings from
40 speakers in Columbus, OH. The speech has been orthographically
transcribed and phonetically labeled. Currently the audio files and
transcriptions for 20 talkers are available. For more information, please
visit www.buckeyecorpus.osu.edu. 

Cordially, 
Laura Dilley, Ph.D.

Buckeye Corpus
www.buckeyecorpus.osu.edu
Dept. of Psychology
The Ohio State University
1835 Neil Avenue Mall
Columbus, OH 43210-1222 



Linguistic Field(s): Computational Linguistics
                     Discourse Analysis
                     Phonetics
                     Sociolinguistics
                     Text/Corpus Linguistics

Subject Language(s): English (eng)





 




